<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880310-0157 </DOCNO><HL> Du Pont, British Firm Form Joint Venture </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DD ICI </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> WILMINGTON, Del.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Du Pont Co. said it formed a joint venture with Imperial Chemical Industries Ltd., London, to supply the European automotive coatings industry.    Du Pont said each chemical concern will have a 50% stake in the venture, which will be based in Bonn, West Germany. The venture will build an applications center there at a cost of about $17 million. Additional investment costs, which include the acquisition of a plant from ICI, weren't disclosed.    The venture initially will represent a 10% stake in a market estimated at between $600 million and $700 million, according to Ross W. Fasick, director of Du Pont's finishes division. The market is about $1 billion in the U.S. and Du Pont has an approximately 33% stake, he said.    Mr. Fasick said he believes the venture can double its European market share in five to 10 years. </TEXT></DOC>